        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 13 at 7:03PM EDT until June 13 at 7:45PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 703 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Wellsville,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
East Liverpool, Wellsville, Calcutta, Chester, New Cumberland,
Newell, Irondale, New Manchester, Empire, Stratton, Hammondsville,
La Croft, Glenmoor, Tomlinson Run State Park and Beaver Creek
State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.</instruction>
